WEBVTT

00:00:02.270 --> 00:00:04.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sometimes in service, we meet people

00:00:04.812 --> 00:00:06.979 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who don’t speak the language that we do.

00:00:08.937 --> 00:00:10.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What is it?

00:00:10.812 --> 00:00:14.937 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Wouldn’t it be cool if we had
a translator robot that could help us?

00:00:19.687 --> 00:00:21.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Get out of here, get out of here!

00:00:24.395 --> 00:00:26.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, we can’t use machines to preach.

00:00:26.229 --> 00:00:28.020 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But we have something better!

00:00:28.020 --> 00:00:30.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
JW Language!

00:00:30.104 --> 00:00:32.687 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You can learn to speak to anyone with this!

00:00:32.687 --> 00:00:35.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
First, pick the language you already speak.

00:00:35.854 --> 00:00:38.687 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Second, choose a language you want to learn.

00:00:38.687 --> 00:00:41.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Third, find “Preaching Skills.”

00:00:41.562 --> 00:00:43.187 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What do you need?

00:00:43.187 --> 00:00:44.937 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Greetings and Introductions”!

00:00:44.937 --> 00:00:45.937 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Good.

00:00:45.937 --> 00:00:48.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Because we need to know
how to say hi to them, right?

00:00:48.104 --> 00:00:49.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So let’s look at this one.

00:00:51.895 --> 00:00:53.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is so cool!

00:00:53.895 --> 00:00:56.145 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Wow!
I can talk to Chinese people!

00:01:05.770 --> 00:01:07.395 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s go in service!

00:01:09.604 --> 00:01:11.187 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What is it?

00:01:11.187 --> 00:01:12.479 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Hello.

00:01:12.479 --> 00:01:15.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I am pleased to meet you.

00:01:15.562 --> 00:01:16.729 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Wow!

00:01:16.729 --> 00:01:18.270 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Come in, come in!

00:01:18.270 --> 00:01:19.687 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Come in, come in!

